This paper discusses the advantages of deep learning over shallow learning, which is a topic that falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper specifically focuses on deep convolutional networks, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) tasks. Additionally, the paper discusses the conditions under which deep learning can be exponentially better than shallow learning, which is a topic that falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
